All Classes

  • Class Description
    AllDiagrams
    This interface is used to identify types that should appear in all UML diagrams.
    LexakaiJavadoc
    Indicates that the Javadoc for a given class, interface, enum or method should be considered complete in terms of Javadoc coverage analysis, even if it doesn't meet the heuristic criteria for completeness.
    UmlAggregation
    This annotation is used to indicate that a field references an aggregate object (an object that is dependent on the referring field's class).
    UmlClassDiagram
    Indicates that the annotated type should be included in a UML diagram.
    UmlComposition
    This annotation is used to indicate that a field references an composite object (an object that is *dependent* -- meaning that it has no second purpose -- on the referring field's class).
    UmlDiagramIdentifier
    This interface is used as a base interface for diagram identifiers used by UmlClassDiagram.diagram().
    UmlDiagramRepeater
    Not public API
    UmlExcludeMember
    Excludes the annotated field, method or constructor from all UML diagrams.
    UmlExcludeSuperTypes
    Excludes one or more superclass types of the annotated type from all UML diagrams.
    UmlIncludeMember
    Forces inclusion of the annotated field, method or constructor even if it is excluded for some other reason.
    UmlMethodGroup
    Adds the annotated method to the named method group.
    UmlMethodGroupRepeater
    Not public API
    UmlNote
    Adds a callout note to the annotated class, interface or method.
    UmlNote.Align
    Specifies alignment of this UML note.
    UmlNotPublicApi
    Marks the annotated class, interface, field or method as not being public API.
    UmlRelation
    This annotation is used to indicate that the annotated type, field or method has a relation with the type specified by UmlRelation.referent().
    UmlRelationRepeater
    Not public API
